The paper discusses a multi-agent environment that requires a diverse set of tools and methods, including planning, opponent/teammate modeling, game theory, and communication. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and computer vision (cs.CV) (for analyzing the game environment).
